# PART II — CODING RECIPE

## Guardrails (all chunks)
- All randomness via the shared module-level `_rng`. Init generation itself needs no RNG.
- Constants named + commented at module level; no inline literals.
- v1 raises loudly. The ONLY tolerated-failure path is generation-retry-then-skip (M9).
- Contract text is written ONCE and injected everywhere (M3) — no per-operator copies.
- The init-generation prompt must remain ARCHITECTURE-FREE (M6): no model names, no real code
  from any existing candidate. If you find yourself pasting tree code into it, stop.
- Provenance: reuse `make_entry` + `lineage_id` machinery from the grace-period build. Do NOT
  invent a parallel tagging path.
- Do not touch: `choose_operation` waterfall order, `pick_frontier_extremes`, frontier logic,
  metric policy.

